## How the requirements are met

- **Free & premium tiers** — `users.tier` column (`CHECK (tier IN ('free','premium'))`), new sign-ups default to `free`.
- **Premium gating** — the `@premium_required` decorator on `/premium` redirects non-premium users to `/upgrade`.
- **Admin can change tiers** — `/admin` lists all users; `POST /admin/users/<id>/tier` updates a user's tier, protected by `@admin_required`.
- **Different navigation per tier** — `base.html` renders Premium Content vs. Go Premium vs. Admin links based on `g.user.tier`/`is_admin`.
- **SQLite** — `membership.db` created automatically on first run; a default admin (`admin` / `admin123`) is seeded.
- **Runnable on port 5072** — `app.run(port=5072)`, documented in the README.

